WEBVTT

00:04.656 --> 00:04.874
.

00:04.917 --> 00:07.442
- Units in the fourth,
we got a caller

00:07.485 --> 00:08.443
who says his neighbor
won't return his lawnmower.

00:08.486 --> 00:10.358
Caller is at 1266 Mohawk.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.534
Lawnmower is apparently
at 1272...

00:12.577 --> 00:14.623
[voice fades]

00:14.666 --> 00:17.191
[tapping continues]

00:18.061 --> 00:20.281
[radio chatter]

00:20.324 --> 00:21.673
- Units in the vicinity.

00:21.717 --> 00:24.763
[voices distorts]

00:24.807 --> 00:26.852
[tapping continues]

00:26.896 --> 00:29.855
[tense music]

00:29.899 --> 00:36.775
♪

00:42.172 --> 00:45.132
[radio chatter]

00:45.175 --> 00:51.051
♪

01:46.280 --> 01:49.413
[radio chatter]

01:52.808 --> 01:54.462
- Units in the third,
got reports

01:54.505 --> 01:56.377
of the boys selling
on the corner again,

01:56.420 --> 01:57.856
Kedzie and St. Louis.

01:57.900 --> 02:00.816
- Squad 11-47,
do you got a description?

02:00.859 --> 02:07.301
♪

02:13.002 --> 02:15.918
[radio chatter]

02:17.049 --> 02:19.617
- Copy, 46-20.

02:19.661 --> 02:21.924
- Robbery in progress.
RXW Drugs.

02:21.967 --> 02:24.622
1527 Pulaski.
Multiple tickets.

02:24.666 --> 02:26.146
Shot fired
by the pharmacy.

02:26.189 --> 02:27.712
GSW reported.

02:27.756 --> 02:29.453
- 50-21 George.
Hold me down as responding.

02:29.497 --> 02:31.151
Plain clothes.
I'm 10-99.

02:31.194 --> 02:33.153
- Copy, 50-21 George.

02:33.196 --> 02:37.983
♪

02:38.027 --> 02:38.984
[gunshots]

02:39.028 --> 02:40.856
[screaming]

02:40.899 --> 02:42.162
50-21 George, on scene.

02:42.205 --> 02:43.989
The call is bona fide.

02:44.033 --> 02:45.165
Keep the cars rolling.

02:45.208 --> 02:46.383
Go, go, go, go!

02:46.427 --> 02:51.693
♪

02:57.177 --> 02:58.743
[whispers]
Stay down, stay down.

03:03.270 --> 03:04.532
Keep your head down.

03:10.015 --> 03:11.147
[gunshots]

03:11.191 --> 03:12.453
- Aah!

03:15.543 --> 03:16.892
- It's OK.
It's OK. It's OK.

03:16.935 --> 03:18.415
Keep your head down
and stay quiet.

03:20.156 --> 03:22.071
Police.
Drop the weapon.

03:22.114 --> 03:24.247
- No, I can't do that, sir.
- Drop it or I drop you.

03:24.291 --> 03:26.118
- No. Now look,
I am reaching...

03:26.162 --> 03:27.119
- No.
- Slowly.

03:27.163 --> 03:28.251
- Don't do that.
- Slowly.

03:28.295 --> 03:29.383
- Stop.

03:31.689 --> 03:34.431
- Lenny Gibson,
master sergeant, 3rd Cav.

03:34.475 --> 03:36.259
- All right, Lenny,
Jay Halstead, Rangers.

03:36.303 --> 03:37.695
Put it down now.
Slide it over.

03:37.739 --> 03:39.262
- Sir, I am
a good piece of gear.

03:39.306 --> 03:41.395
- Slide it over, Lenny.
Let's go.

03:41.438 --> 03:42.787
Now, Lenny.

03:42.831 --> 03:44.398
Now.

03:45.834 --> 03:47.096
- All right.

03:47.139 --> 03:48.663
All right.

03:48.706 --> 03:49.838
Here.

03:49.881 --> 03:51.448
I engaged two men,
winged one.

03:51.492 --> 03:52.493
They ran in there.

03:52.536 --> 03:53.842
There might be civilians
in there.

03:53.885 --> 03:54.973
It's been a fight.

03:55.017 --> 03:56.801
- OK, Lenny,
I'm gonna move forward.

03:56.845 --> 03:58.368
You clear everybody out
of here behind me

03:58.412 --> 03:59.543
and then you get out too.
Do you understand?

03:59.587 --> 04:01.589
- Copy you.
- Let's move. Go.

04:03.112 --> 04:09.988
♪

04:14.123 --> 04:15.516
[gunshots]

04:15.559 --> 04:17.387
Stay back!
Stay back!

04:17.431 --> 04:19.171
- ¿Lucia? Lucia?

04:19.215 --> 04:20.260
My vida.
- Papi.

04:20.303 --> 04:21.696
- No!
Stay there!

04:21.739 --> 04:22.958
[gunshots]

04:26.744 --> 04:28.746
Jesus, man, what the hell
were you thinking?

04:28.790 --> 04:31.271
- They would have killed her.
Go get those pricks.

04:31.314 --> 04:32.228
- No, I'm staying here.
Stay put.

04:32.272 --> 04:34.317
- Go get them!

04:34.361 --> 04:36.145
- Keep pressure.
Stay put, all right?

04:36.188 --> 04:37.668
- I'm good.
Just go, go, go.

04:37.712 --> 04:39.757
[groans]

04:39.801 --> 04:42.020
[gunshots]

04:42.064 --> 04:44.806
- 50-21, I got shots fired
behind the RXW.

04:44.849 --> 04:47.591
Two offenders fleeing in a blue
sedan, older model, no plate.

04:47.635 --> 04:49.245
They're going northbound
on Franklin now.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.507
These men are wanted
on homicide.

04:50.551 --> 04:52.292
They're armed
and extremely dangerous.

04:52.335 --> 04:59.429
♪

05:05.957 --> 05:09.526
[indistinct chatter]

05:09.570 --> 05:10.962
- What did the paramedics say?

05:11.006 --> 05:12.312
- Baby's gonna be OK.

05:12.355 --> 05:14.792
They're checking her for shock.

05:14.836 --> 05:17.317
- You sure you're OK?
- Yeah.

05:17.360 --> 05:19.101
This guy Lenny,

05:19.144 --> 05:21.451
he just took two bullets
for her like it was nothing.

05:21.495 --> 05:23.148
It was like a war zone.

05:23.192 --> 05:25.107
These guys unloaded,
and then Lenny just--he moved.

05:25.150 --> 05:28.110
I haven't seen anything like
that since I was overseas.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.551
Voight's here.

05:39.904 --> 05:41.384
- You good?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

05:41.428 --> 05:42.733
BOLO's out.
- Good.

05:42.777 --> 05:43.995
- Hey.

05:44.039 --> 05:46.476
Went down just like
a good Samaritan said.

05:46.520 --> 05:48.260
- OK, so there's no audio,

05:48.304 --> 05:51.263
but it looks like our offenders
make some sort of demand.

05:51.307 --> 05:53.178
The pharmacist fights back.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.355
All hell breaks loose.

05:57.226 --> 06:00.142
- All right, now,
keep your eye on the other guy.

06:01.883 --> 06:03.493
- That shot came from Lenny?
- Yeah.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.147
Caught him
completely off guard.

06:05.190 --> 06:07.758
- That's how they ended up
in the storage area.

06:07.802 --> 06:08.977
If Lenny hadn't engaged...

06:09.020 --> 06:10.718
- More innocent people
would have died.

06:10.761 --> 06:11.936
- Yeah.

06:11.980 --> 06:13.460
- Yo, yo.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.375
I got a witness who was
at the pharmacy the whole time

06:15.418 --> 06:16.724
saying she saw the whole thing.

06:16.767 --> 06:18.682
The offenders are looking
for pseudoephedrine.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.118
- They're cooking meth.

06:20.162 --> 06:21.685
- That's why the pharmacist
keeps it in the vault.

06:21.729 --> 06:23.774
She wouldn't open it for them,
so...

06:23.818 --> 06:25.602
- All right, so get on the horn
with Narcotics.

06:25.646 --> 06:26.603
Check their radar.

06:26.647 --> 06:28.953
Anyone with a meth sheet.

06:28.997 --> 06:30.694
And one of the offenders
got shot,

06:30.738 --> 06:33.001
so have the lab run any blood

06:33.044 --> 06:34.306
that doesn't match
the pharmacist.

06:34.350 --> 06:36.570
Could pop.
- All right.

06:36.613 --> 06:39.399
- Lenny Gibson--
he gonna make it?

06:39.442 --> 06:41.531
- Med says touch and go.

06:41.575 --> 06:43.446
- Well, get down there,
see what he can offer.

06:51.106 --> 06:52.542
- Mr. Gibson is
on plenty of meds,

06:52.586 --> 06:54.283
but he's alert right now.

06:54.326 --> 06:55.327
- Family here?

06:55.371 --> 06:56.981
- His wife's been here.

06:57.025 --> 06:59.767
Went home to get some stuff
for him, check on the kids.

07:02.030 --> 07:03.945
Some friends
from Mr. Gibson's army days

07:03.988 --> 07:06.469
kind of keeping watch,
I guess.

07:06.513 --> 07:07.949
Go on in.

07:15.130 --> 07:17.480
- Hey.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.569
Jay, right?
- Mm-hmm.

07:19.613 --> 07:21.092
How are you feeling?

07:21.136 --> 07:22.572
- Oh, man.

07:22.616 --> 07:24.705
[groans]
Like five bucks.

07:24.748 --> 07:26.794
- This is my partner,
Detective Upton.

07:26.837 --> 07:29.536
- Hey, Lenny.
I heard a lot about you.

07:29.579 --> 07:31.102
You did a real good thing.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.236
We just have a couple questions
for you

07:34.279 --> 07:36.499
to help us catch these guys.

07:36.543 --> 07:37.979
- Fire away.

07:38.022 --> 07:39.981
- All right,
before it all went down,

07:40.024 --> 07:41.635
did you hear them say anything?

07:41.678 --> 07:44.420
Did they have an accent,
anything like that?

07:44.464 --> 07:47.075
- No, no.

07:47.118 --> 07:50.034
I was on the other side
of the store.

07:50.078 --> 07:51.471
I was--

07:51.514 --> 07:54.517
I was just grabbing a pop.

07:54.561 --> 07:56.432
And then I--

07:56.476 --> 07:57.781
I heard the shots,
and it was,

07:57.825 --> 08:02.786
well, you know,
game on.

08:02.830 --> 08:05.267
- Did you see their faces
without the masks?

08:05.310 --> 08:06.398
- No.

08:06.442 --> 08:08.575
- Any descriptors at all?

08:08.618 --> 08:10.925
- No.

08:10.968 --> 08:12.492
I'm sorry.

08:12.535 --> 08:13.667
It was too fast.

08:13.710 --> 08:16.321
- Hey, don't be sorry,
all right?

08:16.365 --> 08:19.281
Just hang tough.
Rest up.

08:21.239 --> 08:22.937
- Hey.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.592
Let's do it again sometime.

08:25.635 --> 08:26.897
- You bet.

08:35.036 --> 08:36.907
- Excuse me.

08:36.951 --> 08:39.170
I'm Nolan,
Lenny's buddy.

08:39.214 --> 08:41.172
Did you find
these sons of bitches?

08:41.216 --> 08:42.522
- We're working on it.

08:42.565 --> 08:43.958
You serve together?

08:44.001 --> 08:46.264
- All did a three-year hitch
together in the sandbox.

08:46.308 --> 08:48.832
- Me too, 75th Rangers.
Korengal mostly.

08:48.876 --> 08:50.225
- Hooah.

08:51.705 --> 08:53.184
- You all still active duty?

08:53.228 --> 08:54.664
- AGR.

08:54.708 --> 08:57.667
Hooked in with Joint Forces,
Narcotics ops.

08:57.711 --> 09:00.540
Multinational cartel targets.

09:00.583 --> 09:02.977
- Lenny too?
- Nah.

09:03.020 --> 09:04.979
But he's the most decorated
of all of us.

09:05.022 --> 09:07.111
Defused IEDs for our unit.

09:07.155 --> 09:09.810
But he did his time.

09:09.853 --> 09:11.289
He did it well.

09:12.987 --> 09:14.728
- Thanks for looking
after his family.

09:17.861 --> 09:20.168
- This is two months ago
in Brighton Park.

09:20.211 --> 09:22.474
This is two weeks later
down in Chatham.

09:22.518 --> 09:24.041
Robbery-homicide
worked both of them.

09:24.085 --> 09:25.695
- Same height,
weight, build.

09:25.739 --> 09:27.131
Same freaky mask,
same weapons.

09:27.175 --> 09:29.873
- Same target--
pseudoephedrine.

09:29.917 --> 09:31.745
They boosted
30,000 cold medicine pills

09:31.788 --> 09:33.224
in these two robberies alone.

09:33.268 --> 09:35.444
- Oh, so this latest robbery
was an escalation?

09:35.487 --> 09:36.750
- Yeah, so they started out

09:36.793 --> 09:38.229
by hitting
pharmaceutical transport trucks

09:38.273 --> 09:39.883
on the way
to the big box stores.

09:39.927 --> 09:41.929
But last month,
the stores hired off-duty cops

09:41.972 --> 09:43.452
to escort those trucks.

09:43.495 --> 09:45.367
So this time, they waited
for the stuff to be delivered.

09:45.410 --> 09:48.065
Escorts left, heat died down.
Then they hit it.

09:48.109 --> 09:50.677
- But we can't move yet on
any of the previous robberies

09:50.720 --> 09:52.548
on our BOLO, witnesses.

09:52.592 --> 09:54.071
- Just got a call.

09:54.115 --> 09:57.945
Guy at a junkyard in Fuller
Park saw the RXW job on TV.

09:57.988 --> 10:00.425
Claims somebody just
ditched our getaway car.

10:00.469 --> 10:01.688
- Thanks, Trudy.
- Yeah.

10:01.731 --> 10:03.864
- Go.

10:03.907 --> 10:06.344
- Every day is one big blur
of crap on tires.

10:06.388 --> 10:08.738
But a 12-year-old Corolla
with a jangly bumper?

10:08.782 --> 10:10.305
That rang a bell
from what I'd seen on the news.

10:10.348 --> 10:11.436
- Do you know the guy
who dropped it?

10:11.480 --> 10:12.699
- Just some guy.

10:12.742 --> 10:14.657
- Get a name?
- No, we don't take names.

10:14.701 --> 10:15.745
Want to get rid
of your clunker?

10:15.789 --> 10:17.442
We take your clunker.
That's the deal.

10:17.486 --> 10:19.923
No, I tried to stall him for
a bit, but he got all cagey.

10:19.967 --> 10:21.098
Must have left
about 10 minutes ago.

10:21.142 --> 10:22.447
- You got cameras around here?

10:22.491 --> 10:24.449
- Don't believe
in that big-brother stuff.

10:24.493 --> 10:26.364
Car should be right up here
around the corner.

10:28.584 --> 10:29.629
- Smoke.

10:29.672 --> 10:32.370
- Oh, no!

10:32.414 --> 10:33.763
- That's the car.

10:33.807 --> 10:34.938
That's the car!
That's the car!

10:34.982 --> 10:36.113
- Back up.
- Jesus.

10:36.157 --> 10:37.549
The whole place could go up.
- Back up.

10:37.593 --> 10:39.029
Back up!

10:40.683 --> 10:42.293
50-21 Henry, emergency.

10:42.337 --> 10:45.601
We need CFD to 1314 Vienna,
southeast corner of the yard.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.777
We got a vehicle on fire.
- Copy.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.300
- Jay, whoa.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.214
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hey!

10:53.217 --> 10:55.089
Jay?
- Hailey, we got to try.

10:55.132 --> 10:57.657
There's probably evidence
in there.

10:57.700 --> 10:58.788
- Come on.
Leave it.

10:58.832 --> 11:00.529
Hey, leave it.
Leave it.

11:00.572 --> 11:02.792
Get out!
Let's go!

11:02.836 --> 11:06.187
[explosion]

11:06.230 --> 11:13.150
♪

11:17.677 --> 11:17.807
.

11:17.851 --> 11:20.201
- So he just walked off
after he got cagey with you?

11:20.244 --> 11:21.506
- Did he catch a ride
with someone?

11:21.550 --> 11:22.594
Was someone waiting for him?
- I don't know.

11:22.638 --> 11:23.726
He was there,
and then he wasn't.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.293
- Anything's gonna help us.
Was he fat?

11:25.336 --> 11:26.773
Was he skinny?
Did he have a tattoo?

11:26.816 --> 11:28.731
- He was just
a basic white dude, I guess.

11:28.775 --> 11:30.472
Tall, I guess, thin.
- All right, thanks.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.474
We're gonna give you a call.

11:32.517 --> 11:34.389
- Well, if there's no cameras
on the street out front,

11:34.432 --> 11:36.521
there's no telling
if anybody ever saw this dude.

11:36.565 --> 11:37.871
He could be far as hell by now.

11:37.914 --> 11:39.960
- Hey, techs think
they found a good print

11:40.003 --> 11:40.961
on the engine block.

11:41.004 --> 11:42.179
Print survived the fire.

11:42.223 --> 11:43.659
It looks like
our crew left it there

11:43.703 --> 11:45.574
when they were carving VINs
off the getaway car.

11:45.617 --> 11:46.880
They're running it now.

11:48.490 --> 11:50.318
The print on the getaway car
is a dead match

11:50.361 --> 11:52.276
to Calvin Morrell, 27.

11:52.320 --> 11:53.843
He's got a long sheet,
minor stuff.

11:53.887 --> 11:57.629
But the kicker?
He's hooked to meth.

11:57.673 --> 11:59.719
- 6'4".
A beanpole.

11:59.762 --> 12:02.373
Strong match for the offender
Lenny Gibson winged.

12:02.417 --> 12:04.854
- Active bench warrant
for his arrest.

12:04.898 --> 12:06.203
- Scoop him up.

12:10.207 --> 12:11.469
- There it is.

12:14.037 --> 12:15.473
- Ready?
- Yep.

12:15.517 --> 12:16.431
- [grunts]
- Whoa, whoa.

12:16.474 --> 12:17.824
- Calvin Morrell!

12:17.867 --> 12:19.260
- Chicago PD!

12:21.044 --> 12:22.611
[rock music playing]

12:22.654 --> 12:23.568
- In here.

12:24.918 --> 12:25.875
Gun!

12:27.703 --> 12:29.487
Hands out.
Hands out.

12:29.531 --> 12:30.793
Drop the pipe.
Drop it!

12:34.492 --> 12:36.407
- Is this about that warrant?

12:36.451 --> 12:37.931
- You're under arrest
for armed robbery, murder,

12:37.974 --> 12:40.150
and the attempted murder
of a Chicago police officer.

12:40.194 --> 12:41.369
- What?

12:41.412 --> 12:43.545
What the hell
are you talking about?

12:46.113 --> 12:47.854
I'm not saying I'm a saint.

12:47.897 --> 12:49.638
I'm just saying
I've got nothing to do

12:49.681 --> 12:51.553
with a robbery
at a drugstore.

12:51.596 --> 12:54.121
- Your prints are
all over the car

12:54.164 --> 12:55.600
that was used in the robbery.

12:55.644 --> 12:57.559
- A woman was killed.
Another man's in the ICU.

12:57.602 --> 12:58.865
Do you understand the stakes
that we're talking about?

12:58.908 --> 13:00.475
You're looking
at murder, Calvin.

13:03.783 --> 13:06.916
- Look.
I stole that car, OK?

13:06.960 --> 13:10.093
And then I sold it,
like, two weeks ago

13:10.137 --> 13:11.573
just to make rent.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.488
- OK, sure.
Who'd you sell it to?

13:13.531 --> 13:15.316
- Come on.
- Who'd you sell it to?

13:15.359 --> 13:17.753
- I answer that,
it's a death sentence.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.363
This guy--

13:19.407 --> 13:21.757
he'd beat me to death.

13:21.801 --> 13:24.325
- Preliminary arson report
on the getaway car.

13:24.368 --> 13:26.196
It's real thin,
nothing to go on.

13:26.240 --> 13:29.852
- Thanks.
- How's it going in there?

13:29.896 --> 13:31.593
- The problem is
the car theft alone.

13:31.636 --> 13:32.594
That's your third strike.

13:32.637 --> 13:33.769
You're a habitual offender.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.379
And now,
you're downstate for life.

13:35.423 --> 13:36.728
- What?

13:36.772 --> 13:38.861
I didn't have anything to do
with the robbery.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.254
It was just the car.

13:40.297 --> 13:42.996
- You're right, man.
It's a bad way to get life.

13:43.039 --> 13:45.128
So I'm gonna give you
a way out, OK?

13:45.172 --> 13:47.565
I'm gonna trash
the warrant we used for today.

13:47.609 --> 13:49.916
I'm gonna drop the charges
for the car.

13:49.959 --> 13:52.005
I'll expunge your record.

13:52.048 --> 13:55.269
All you got to do
is give me that name.

13:55.312 --> 13:58.881
[tense music]

13:58.925 --> 14:03.712
♪

14:03.755 --> 14:06.628
- Jay, you can't make the
promise you just made in there.

14:06.671 --> 14:07.934
We can't keep it.
You know that.

14:07.977 --> 14:09.761
- I have zero intention
keeping that promise.

14:09.805 --> 14:10.980
It worked, though.
- Yeah.

14:11.024 --> 14:12.503
Until it gets thrown out.
- It won't.

14:12.547 --> 14:13.722
- You don't know that.

14:18.596 --> 14:21.338
- Morrell sold the car
to this man, Benjamin Watt.

14:21.382 --> 14:23.297
Pride of Rogers Park.
No sheet.

14:23.340 --> 14:25.690
He's a person of interest
in our narcotics investigation,

14:25.734 --> 14:27.910
targeting meth
linked to dozens of ODs.

14:27.954 --> 14:29.738
The problem is they were
never able to charge him.

14:29.781 --> 14:31.087
But he's a great physical match

14:31.131 --> 14:32.654
for offender number one,
the guy who shot Lenny.

14:32.697 --> 14:34.351
- Morrell ID Watt by name?

14:34.395 --> 14:35.918
- And in a six pack.
This is our guy.

14:35.962 --> 14:37.267
- He looks good for it,
but we have

14:37.311 --> 14:40.053
zero actionable evidence
tying Watt to that RXW.

14:40.096 --> 14:41.141
- None.
- All right.

14:41.184 --> 14:42.490
Then let's find some.

14:42.533 --> 14:44.318
Dig in to Watt.
Sit on his ass.

14:44.361 --> 14:45.623
Shadow him.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.500
- This just in:
according to Torres,

14:52.543 --> 14:56.156
Benjamin Watt has just
arrived at the gym.

14:56.199 --> 14:57.374
- DEA's a dry well.

14:57.418 --> 14:58.723
- All right, thanks.

14:58.767 --> 15:01.552
Well, my CI says
we're on the right path.

15:01.596 --> 15:03.163
West Garfield,
Logan Square.

15:03.206 --> 15:04.991
Benjamin Watt is the candyman,

15:05.034 --> 15:07.863
but he's got nothing
for us to jump into.

15:11.519 --> 15:18.656
♪

15:24.227 --> 15:25.576
[phone buzzing]

15:38.372 --> 15:40.635
- Hey, what's going on?
What are we doing down here?

15:40.678 --> 15:42.985
- I looked through
Ben Watt's cell transactions.

15:43.029 --> 15:44.552
- Found something?

15:44.595 --> 15:46.336
- Something
you're not gonna like.

15:46.380 --> 15:47.555
- What?

15:48.773 --> 15:51.211
- Two hours
before the RXW job,

15:51.254 --> 15:54.040
Watt sent $400...

15:54.083 --> 15:55.737
to Lenny Gibson.

15:56.999 --> 15:59.219
I don't think
he's just a good Samaritan.

15:59.262 --> 16:01.569
I think he's in on the robbery.

16:01.612 --> 16:05.965
♪

16:11.274 --> 16:11.448
.

16:11.492 --> 16:13.537
- You said
you were picking up a pop?

16:13.581 --> 16:14.930
- Yeah, that's right.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.888
- Had you paid for it yet
when everything happened?

16:16.932 --> 16:19.326
Had you opened it?

16:19.369 --> 16:20.980
- No.

16:21.023 --> 16:23.025
Why are we talking about pop?

16:23.069 --> 16:24.940
- Because they keep the pop
in a display case

16:24.984 --> 16:27.160
next to the pharmacy.

16:27.203 --> 16:29.162
And that's a completely
different part of the store

16:29.205 --> 16:32.034
than you were in
when you engaged the robbers.

16:32.078 --> 16:34.080
- [stammers]

16:34.123 --> 16:36.691
Maybe I did pay.
I don't know.

16:36.734 --> 16:38.171
- Lenny?

16:38.214 --> 16:40.564
- Come on, man.

16:40.608 --> 16:43.785
No more lies, please.

16:43.828 --> 16:46.788
[somber music]

16:46.831 --> 16:50.487
♪

16:50.531 --> 16:53.447
- [sobbing]

16:54.535 --> 16:55.579
I'm dying.

16:55.623 --> 16:56.624
- Don't say that.

16:56.667 --> 16:58.147
- No, I am.

16:58.191 --> 16:59.583
I can feel it.

17:01.672 --> 17:03.022
Please.

17:05.241 --> 17:07.939
Please don't tell my family,

17:07.983 --> 17:11.508
my kids,
what I did.

17:11.552 --> 17:12.466
Please.

17:14.163 --> 17:16.165
- Just tell us what happened.

17:18.994 --> 17:22.476
- I was just lookout...

17:24.826 --> 17:29.048
To tell him when
the cold medicine was unloaded.

17:31.311 --> 17:33.356
They swore
no one would get hurt.

17:36.577 --> 17:40.276
When I saw him
shoot that pharmacist...

17:43.323 --> 17:45.107
That, I couldn't take.

17:51.722 --> 17:55.813
I did the right thing
when it counted.

17:55.857 --> 17:57.163
Didn't I do that?

17:59.600 --> 18:01.558
- Who hired you?
Who are the other robbers?

18:05.910 --> 18:07.564
Was it him?

18:09.044 --> 18:10.132
[monitor beeping rapidly]

18:10.176 --> 18:11.438
- Lenny? Lenny?

18:11.481 --> 18:12.830
Help! Help!
- We need some help in here.

18:12.874 --> 18:14.136
- Help!
Just hang on.

18:14.180 --> 18:15.355
Hang on, man.
Hang on.

18:15.398 --> 18:16.878
- Give us space
to keep him alive.

18:16.921 --> 18:18.619
- Lenny! Lenny! Lenny! Lenny!
- No, come on. Come on.

18:18.662 --> 18:20.099
We got to let them work.
- Out, out, out. We got him.

18:20.142 --> 18:21.622
- What's happening? Lenny!
- We got to let them work.

18:21.665 --> 18:27.584
♪

18:27.628 --> 18:29.586
I'll call Voight.

18:29.630 --> 18:31.022
- What? About what?

18:31.066 --> 18:32.154
- About Lenny.

18:32.198 --> 18:33.373
He just confessed
to being the lookout.

18:33.416 --> 18:34.591
We need to get a warrant.

18:34.635 --> 18:36.332
We need to search
his house, his phone.

18:36.376 --> 18:37.855
He must have alerted
the rest of the crew

18:37.899 --> 18:39.727
when the pills arrived;
so we get something like that,

18:39.770 --> 18:42.860
we get Watt,
and then we can make the case.

18:42.904 --> 18:44.558
- No, no.

18:44.601 --> 18:46.168
- No?
What do you mean no?

18:46.212 --> 18:48.736
- Hailey, he's dying.

18:48.779 --> 18:50.868
We can't take his name too.

18:50.912 --> 18:53.175
- That's not your call.

18:53.219 --> 18:57.310
- One bad act doesn't
make you a bad person.

18:57.353 --> 18:59.094
You and I both know that.

19:01.444 --> 19:02.445
- What?

19:03.968 --> 19:06.449
Jay, can I talk to you
for a second, please?

19:07.798 --> 19:09.713
What's going on with you? This
isn't you.

19:09.757 --> 19:10.758
- What isn't?

19:10.801 --> 19:13.326
- Everything lately.

19:13.369 --> 19:15.241
Skirting evidence,

19:15.284 --> 19:17.068
lying to me,
no-knocks,

19:17.112 --> 19:18.635
making bad deals in the box,

19:18.679 --> 19:20.724
you and Voight,
you pulling away from me--

19:20.768 --> 19:22.422
all of it.

19:22.465 --> 19:24.206
I don't know what's changed
or what's going on with you.

19:24.250 --> 19:26.077
I don't know what to do,

19:26.121 --> 19:28.079
but I'm here,
and I want to help.

19:28.123 --> 19:30.691
[phone buzzes]

19:30.734 --> 19:31.648
- Halstead.

19:34.042 --> 19:35.217
OK.

19:40.091 --> 19:41.571
OK.

19:41.615 --> 19:42.616
Thanks.

19:45.793 --> 19:46.837
Lenny's dead.

19:48.230 --> 19:49.449
That's it.

19:50.928 --> 19:55.759
Hailey, he gave his life
for that woman at the scene.

19:55.803 --> 19:59.241
We got nothing more
that we can take from him.

19:59.285 --> 20:01.809
And we can make the case
another way.

20:01.852 --> 20:03.419
So let's do that.

20:03.463 --> 20:04.594
Come on.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.558
- All right, what did we get
from Ballistics?

20:11.601 --> 20:13.037
- No match
for the drugstore slugs.

20:13.081 --> 20:15.823
And no shots fired
during the earlier robberies.

20:15.866 --> 20:17.955
- All right, what about
the ping order on Watt's cell?

20:17.999 --> 20:19.392
- Sorry, we got nothing on GPS.

20:19.435 --> 20:20.958
They must have used
burners for this job.

20:21.002 --> 20:23.309
- All right,
Watt bought that getaway car.

20:23.352 --> 20:25.136
That is receipt
of stolen property.

20:25.180 --> 20:26.486
Pick them up on that.

20:26.529 --> 20:28.096
Then we'll make him
for the charges that matter.

20:28.139 --> 20:29.184
- I tried that, boss.

20:29.228 --> 20:30.838
ASA said
that we have zero evidence

20:30.881 --> 20:34.145
that Watt knew
that the car was stolen.

20:34.189 --> 20:35.843
- I got two dead civilians

20:35.886 --> 20:37.366
and 30,000 pills out there

20:37.410 --> 20:40.282
just killing people
all over Chicago.

20:40.326 --> 20:42.284
So drill down.

20:42.328 --> 20:44.808
Find the thing
that makes this case.

20:47.637 --> 20:48.943
- We might have another one.

20:48.986 --> 20:50.292
- Damn.
Drugstore?

20:50.336 --> 20:52.033
- Elixir Pharmacy,
Archer Heights.

20:52.076 --> 20:53.469
Shots fired.
Civilians down.

20:55.471 --> 20:58.561
[indistinct chatter]

21:01.521 --> 21:02.826
- What do you got?

21:02.870 --> 21:05.438
- Two offenders, armed,
demanded pills.

21:05.481 --> 21:07.527
Pharmacist balked.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.964
They shot some poor old lady
right in front of them.

21:10.007 --> 21:12.836
Lady was buying batteries
for her hearing aids.

21:12.880 --> 21:14.098
- Pseudoephedrine?

21:14.142 --> 21:15.230
- What?

21:15.274 --> 21:16.753
- The pills they were after?

21:16.797 --> 21:17.885
- Yeah, that's it.

21:17.928 --> 21:20.627
Doesn't exactly
roll off the tongue.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.455
Pharmacist turned over the
pills so no one else got hurt.

21:22.498 --> 21:24.152
Bad guys took off that way.

21:24.195 --> 21:26.676
Sounds like this guy got in the
way, so they took him out too.

21:26.720 --> 21:29.200
- They were wearing masks?
- Yeah, that's right.

21:29.244 --> 21:30.898
White plastic mask
with hoodies.

21:30.941 --> 21:32.073
How do you know that?

21:32.116 --> 21:36.643
♪

21:42.562 --> 21:42.953
.

21:42.997 --> 21:44.781
- I don't get it.

21:44.825 --> 21:45.869
You know, we worked
the hell out of this thing,

21:45.913 --> 21:47.480
and it's the same deal
we had before.

21:47.523 --> 21:49.133
- Nobody saw their faces.

21:49.177 --> 21:51.658
We don't even have enough
for a BOLO on the getaway car.

21:51.701 --> 21:53.007
- They're either
the best in the business

21:53.050 --> 21:54.704
or the luckiest pricks
on the planet.

21:56.315 --> 21:57.403
- For all we know,
we could have

21:57.446 --> 21:59.448
cracked this thing
and saved two lives.

21:59.492 --> 22:02.233
- You don't know that's true.
- You don't know it's not.

22:02.277 --> 22:04.845
You need to secure the warrant
on Lenny, or I will.

22:04.888 --> 22:07.761
It's the right thing to do.

22:07.804 --> 22:08.936
- The right thing?

22:11.939 --> 22:14.855
OK, these guys aren't
gonna hit again today.

22:14.898 --> 22:16.030
Just give me a few hours.

22:16.073 --> 22:17.423
I'm gonna find a way
to work it.

22:18.772 --> 22:19.990
- OK.

22:31.524 --> 22:33.264
- Nolan?

22:33.308 --> 22:34.744
Jay Halstead.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.399
You still standing watch, huh?

22:37.443 --> 22:39.401
- Something like that.

22:39.445 --> 22:42.230
After Lenny went,
I figured I'd stick around

22:42.273 --> 22:45.276
for a few more days
and see what Lorenza needs.

22:45.320 --> 22:46.756
- Yeah.

22:47.844 --> 22:50.673
- This is
Lenny's accounting system.

22:50.717 --> 22:53.197
Their whole life in this box.

22:53.241 --> 22:54.416
Trying to make sense of it

22:54.460 --> 22:56.984
so I can get
Lenny's life insurance moving.

22:58.159 --> 23:00.422
- I'm sorry Lenny's gone, man.

23:04.948 --> 23:07.386
- Imagine I know
why you're here.

23:09.344 --> 23:11.781
- You knew he was involved
in the robbery?

23:13.870 --> 23:16.133
- No.

23:16.177 --> 23:18.527
I knew he was in pain.

23:18.571 --> 23:20.137
I know when people are in pain,

23:20.181 --> 23:23.924
sometimes they do things
they may not otherwise do.

23:23.967 --> 23:26.579
Lenny came home rough
from there.

23:26.622 --> 23:30.496
He couldn't hold down a job,
couldn't pay the bills.

23:30.539 --> 23:33.063
I couldn't get him cleared
to work with us.

23:33.107 --> 23:37.590
The electric got cut,
daycare bills unpaid.

23:37.633 --> 23:39.940
I think he got desperate.

23:45.032 --> 23:48.470
Look, if you do this,

23:48.514 --> 23:52.474
the army will say Lenny's death
was due to misconduct.

23:52.518 --> 23:55.259
- Lenny's death was due
to misconduct.

23:55.303 --> 23:57.958
- And once the army
makes that official,

23:58.001 --> 24:00.003
this family,

24:00.047 --> 24:02.876
they'll lose everything--

24:02.919 --> 24:06.401
his pension,
his life insurance.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.317
You know
what'll happen to them.

24:09.360 --> 24:13.800
Lenny was a good man,
an honorable man.

24:13.843 --> 24:16.237
He just got chewed up.

24:22.373 --> 24:27.204
- Lenny was involved
with the robbery?

24:27.248 --> 24:28.554
- Yes.

24:28.597 --> 24:31.557
[tense music]

24:31.600 --> 24:38.389
♪

24:48.095 --> 24:52.229
Listen, I need you
to unlock Lenny's phone,

24:52.273 --> 24:55.537
his account to his computer,
his entire life for me--

24:55.581 --> 24:58.540
but just for me.

24:58.584 --> 25:00.237
- What does that mean?

25:01.848 --> 25:05.460
- It means I'm gonna
keep Lenny's name out of this.

25:09.725 --> 25:12.032
- You're allowed to do that?

25:12.075 --> 25:19.213
♪

27:14.067 --> 27:15.372
- Damn it.

27:18.637 --> 27:20.029
It's Benjamin Watt.

27:33.173 --> 27:34.914
Driver's gotta be
the second offender.

27:34.957 --> 27:36.132
- All right.
Go get him out of there.

27:36.176 --> 27:37.830
I'll handle the driver.

27:37.873 --> 27:44.053
♪

28:14.475 --> 28:15.824
Oh, hey.

28:15.868 --> 28:17.565
Hey.

28:17.608 --> 28:19.698
Excuse me.
I'm sorry to bother you.

28:19.741 --> 28:20.873
- Hey, get the hell out
of here.

28:20.916 --> 28:22.396
- Hey, I'm lost.

28:22.439 --> 28:25.094
Look, I'm just looking
for this diner.

28:25.138 --> 28:28.141
It's Pat's or Matt's
or something.

28:28.184 --> 28:29.055
Supposed to be around here.
- What?

28:29.098 --> 28:30.796
- You move, you die.

28:30.839 --> 28:33.015
You understand?

28:33.059 --> 28:34.756
Just nod.

28:34.800 --> 28:35.975
Good.

28:36.018 --> 28:38.717
OK, put your hand
on the wheel real slow.

28:38.760 --> 28:45.680
♪

28:57.039 --> 28:58.911
[rustling]

28:58.954 --> 29:02.088
[suspenseful music]

29:02.131 --> 29:07.267
♪

29:07.310 --> 29:10.749
[both grunting]

29:42.998 --> 29:44.695
- Aah!

29:44.739 --> 29:48.351
[both grunting]

30:12.027 --> 30:13.115
- [yelps]

30:13.159 --> 30:20.253
♪

30:26.041 --> 30:26.259
.

30:26.302 --> 30:28.522
[tense music]

30:28.565 --> 30:35.485
♪

30:40.926 --> 30:42.884
- Call it in.

30:47.280 --> 30:49.891
Hailey, we got to move fast.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.980
Call it in right now.

30:58.030 --> 31:00.510
- 50-21 Henry.

31:00.554 --> 31:02.425
- Go with your traffic.

31:02.469 --> 31:04.297
- My partner,
50-21 George,

31:04.340 --> 31:09.041
asked me to roll the crime lab
to 216 Highway 49.

31:09.084 --> 31:11.521
Apparent homicide victim.
Multiple puncture wounds.

31:11.565 --> 31:12.653
- Copy.

31:12.696 --> 31:13.915
- Where is the other guy,
the driver?

31:13.959 --> 31:15.569
- He's cuffed to the car.

31:15.612 --> 31:18.789
- Squad, we got one in custody.
We're gonna need transport.

31:18.833 --> 31:23.142
Be advised this is an ongoing
confidential investigation.

31:23.185 --> 31:25.971
50-21 is on the scene
and has command.

31:26.014 --> 31:29.017
- Copy that.
Making notifications.

31:30.976 --> 31:33.369
- OK.

31:33.413 --> 31:34.501
OK.

31:37.460 --> 31:40.333
OK, in the course
of our investigation,

31:40.376 --> 31:42.944
we obtained
credible information

31:42.988 --> 31:46.861
that the robbery crew was using
this location as a stash house

31:46.905 --> 31:48.515
and a cooking lab.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.263
- Upon arrival,

31:57.306 --> 32:00.005
we observed
suspicious activity.

32:00.048 --> 32:03.008
- Uh-huh.
- A suspected rip.

32:03.051 --> 32:04.879
Detective Halstead
tailed a suspect inside.

32:04.923 --> 32:06.185
Heard a struggle.

32:06.228 --> 32:07.664
Discovered the man
on the ground bleeding out.

32:07.708 --> 32:09.623
- Uh-huh.

32:09.666 --> 32:12.974
And Detective Halstead
was unable to give chase

32:13.018 --> 32:15.368
because he had to stop
and render aid.

32:16.717 --> 32:18.458
The victim died.

32:18.501 --> 32:20.982
Suspicious suspect
made good his escape.

32:21.026 --> 32:22.592
Identity unknown.

32:24.377 --> 32:27.206
- We recovered stolen meds,
cooking lab.

32:27.249 --> 32:29.338
Got one in custody.

32:31.601 --> 32:33.429
- That's good.

32:33.473 --> 32:35.605
That's good.
No holes, no fat.

32:35.649 --> 32:37.738
Jay?

32:37.781 --> 32:39.348
Jay!

32:39.392 --> 32:42.569
Jay, are you getting this?

32:42.612 --> 32:43.613
Jay?

32:48.096 --> 32:50.142
Jay, we got to be
in agreement here.

32:51.970 --> 32:53.406
- We're doing it again.

32:53.449 --> 32:54.624
- What?

32:54.668 --> 32:56.278
- We're doing it again.
- Listen to me.

32:56.322 --> 32:58.846
We do not have a lot of time.

32:58.889 --> 33:00.543
Now give me the knife.
Let's go.

33:07.811 --> 33:09.465
- What the hell am I doing?

33:11.032 --> 33:12.425
- Jay, give him your knife.

33:12.468 --> 33:14.253
- Listen, you got
to dust yourself off,

33:14.296 --> 33:16.559
get yourself in check.

33:16.603 --> 33:17.996
We got to go.

33:22.217 --> 33:25.220
- Jay, it's gonna to be OK.

33:25.264 --> 33:27.135
You're gonna be OK.

33:29.007 --> 33:31.444
- Give me the goddamn knife!

33:35.578 --> 33:37.015
Now!

33:39.365 --> 33:42.716
Jay, just give me the knife.

33:45.849 --> 33:52.595
♪

34:30.894 --> 34:32.200
[elevator dings]

34:33.593 --> 34:35.029
- Oh, hey.

34:35.073 --> 34:36.291
Come on in.

34:40.904 --> 34:44.343
So, Detective,
what can I do for you?

34:47.737 --> 34:48.738
- Uh...

34:52.220 --> 34:54.309
I'm here to tell the truth.

34:59.401 --> 35:01.795
- Sit down.
Come on.

35:04.189 --> 35:07.366
Your sergeant told me
about this civilian,

35:07.409 --> 35:10.804
how he joined forces with you
at the robbery scene,

35:10.847 --> 35:13.894
sacrificed himself
for this pregnant woman.

35:13.937 --> 35:15.809
It's remarkable.

35:15.852 --> 35:17.898
I'm gonna put Mr. Gibson up
for commendation

35:17.941 --> 35:19.378
through the Good Samaritan Act.

35:19.421 --> 35:21.902
Get a nice ribbon
for his family.

35:21.945 --> 35:25.558
But we're gonna make sure
the army hears about this to,

35:25.601 --> 35:28.430
make sure
his family's taken care of.

35:28.474 --> 35:30.563
From what I understand,

35:30.606 --> 35:32.434
the meth this crew was making

35:32.478 --> 35:35.437
cost a minimum
of 35 deaths from overdose.

35:35.481 --> 35:37.004
We just got an assessment
from Narcotics

35:37.047 --> 35:38.658
that the pills you recovered

35:38.701 --> 35:40.616
would have put another
200 pounds of this stuff

35:40.660 --> 35:42.227
on the street,

35:42.270 --> 35:44.446
so you saved a lot of lives.

35:53.847 --> 35:54.935
- Thank you, sir.

35:54.978 --> 36:01.159
♪

36:01.202 --> 36:02.682
- Now what's this?

36:04.249 --> 36:05.685
- My resignation.

36:10.994 --> 36:13.127
- What?

36:13.171 --> 36:16.217
- I spoke
to Lenny's friend, Nolan.

36:16.261 --> 36:18.176
They need people.

36:18.219 --> 36:19.786
They need soldiers
to run these units,

36:19.829 --> 36:21.527
doing drug interdiction.

36:21.570 --> 36:23.485
- What are you talking about?

36:26.096 --> 36:30.536
- You were right about me.

36:30.579 --> 36:31.885
I changed.

36:31.928 --> 36:32.973
- No, Jay.

36:33.016 --> 36:34.104
I didn't mean this.

36:34.148 --> 36:36.890
I didn't mean resign.

36:36.933 --> 36:38.283
- [voice breaks]
I had to.

36:40.415 --> 36:42.591
It was the right thing to do.

36:48.249 --> 36:51.513
- Nolan put in a call, and...

36:51.557 --> 36:54.299
the army offered me a spot.

36:54.342 --> 36:55.822
I'll run a full squad of guys,

36:55.865 --> 36:58.041
tracking down
the worst cartel targets.

36:58.085 --> 37:01.262
- No, no, no.
Listen to me.

37:01.306 --> 37:05.832
We're gonna get through this,
you and me, together.

37:05.875 --> 37:08.226
OK? We're gonna be fine.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.535
- I took the job.

37:17.235 --> 37:18.888
I'll be posted in Bolivia.

37:23.937 --> 37:25.852
It's black and white.

37:25.895 --> 37:27.201
It's good and bad.

37:27.245 --> 37:31.901
It's right and wrong,
and it's no more of this.

37:31.945 --> 37:33.294
I need that.

37:33.338 --> 37:35.253
I need that back.

37:38.691 --> 37:41.737
- But you can't just leave.

37:41.781 --> 37:43.348
- [sighs]

37:45.088 --> 37:46.916
I fly out today.

37:46.960 --> 37:49.528
- [sobbing] Today?

37:49.571 --> 37:51.007
- It's not forever, OK?

37:51.051 --> 37:54.663
It's eight months,
maybe a little longer.

37:56.404 --> 37:58.711
But I swear to you

37:58.754 --> 38:02.018
that we're gonna
get through this because...

38:02.062 --> 38:04.499
you're the love of my life.

38:04.543 --> 38:05.892
And if I'm yours...

38:05.935 --> 38:07.676
- Of course you are.

38:09.765 --> 38:13.247
- Then you'll know
that you have to let me go.

38:13.291 --> 38:20.385
♪

38:41.971 --> 38:44.887
- [sobbing]

38:56.769 --> 38:57.813
- Hey!

39:07.301 --> 39:09.912
- I thought
you hated long goodbyes.

39:15.004 --> 39:18.530
- You can have any job you want
in our department.

39:20.923 --> 39:24.492
I'd tell you
I'd make sure of it, but...

39:24.536 --> 39:27.495
you don't need me.

39:27.539 --> 39:29.367
You're past that.

39:35.068 --> 39:37.679
If you don't want to be me--
- No.

39:40.073 --> 39:41.901
It's worse than that.

39:44.382 --> 39:45.948
I do.

39:48.951 --> 39:50.736
I do want to be you.

39:53.826 --> 39:57.003
But it's like
you've always told me,

39:57.046 --> 39:58.570
I'm not.

40:00.659 --> 40:03.357
And I shouldn't try.

40:03.401 --> 40:06.316
[somber music]

40:06.360 --> 40:13.454
♪

40:50.230 --> 40:50.709
.

40:50.752 --> 40:53.494
[tense music]

40:53.538 --> 41:00.632
♪

41:19.651 --> 41:22.784
[wolf howls]
